 that of a catalyst: to spur studies of diversities in English (and in other languages), to suggest approaches to adapt, to invite counterargument and developments in analysis.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aEnglish languagexVariationvCongresses. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aEnglish.  aHeterogeneity.  aSociolinguistics.  aTypology.1 aBao, Zhiming, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGreen, Eugene, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGreen, Eugene, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHazen, Kirk, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHinrichs, Lars, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMair, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMesthrie, Rajend, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeyer, Charles F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeyer, Charles F., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNelson, Gerald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTagliamonte, Sali A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWiltshire, Caroline R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Linguistics and Semiotics  2000-2014 (EN)z978311023845708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton Backlist 2000-2015z978311074